Having downloaded the [[ANTLR 3.0]] distribution (<tt>antlr-3.0.tar.gz</tt>) from the [[ANTLR]] website, installation is straightforward.

<pre>tar xzvf antlr-3.0.tar.gz

#Â move expanded archive into position
sudo mv antlr-3.0 /usr/local/

# remove old symbolic link
cd /usr/local/
sudo rm -f antlr

# set up new symbolic link
sudo ln -s antlr-3.0 antlr</pre>

To actually use [[ANTLR]] the jars must be in your classpath:

<pre>export CLASSPATH="/usr/local/antlr/lib/antlr-3.0.jar"
export CLASSPATH="$CLASSPATH:/usr/local/antlr/lib/antlr-2.7.7.jar" 
export CLASSPATH="$CLASSPATH:/usr/local/antlr/lib/antlr-runtime-3.0.jar"
export CLASSPATH="$CLASSPATH:/usr/local/antlr/lib/stringtemplate-3.0.jar"</pre>

These <tt>export</tt> statements can be added to your <tt>~/.bash_profile</tt> if you plan on using [[ANTLR]] often.
